modules.name: Thermite
modules.comments:
This module defines functions for working with React components at a high level:

- `createClass` and `simpleSpec`, which can be used to create a component class
- `render` and `renderTo`, which can be used to render a component class

declarations.comments:
A type synonym for action handlers, which take an action and the current properties
for the component, and return a computation in the `Action` monad.
declarations.title: PerformAction

declarations.comments:
A rendering function, which takes a `Context`, the current state and properties, an array
of child nodes and returns a HTML document.
declarations.title: Render

declarations.comments:
A component specification, which can be passed to `createClass`.

A minimal `Spec` can be built using `simpleSpec`, and extended with optional arguments
using functions in the `Thermite` module.
declarations.title: Spec

declarations.comments: A type synonym for the record type which captures the functions which make up a `Spec`.
declarations.title: SpecRecord

declarations.comments:
Create a minimal `Spec`. The arguments are, in order:

- The initial component state
- A function for performing actions
- A function for rendering the current state as a HTML document

A `Spec` created using this function can be extended with optional properties using other functions
in this module.
declarations.title: simpleSpec

declarations.comments: Extend a `Spec` with an action to run when the component will be mounted.
declarations.title: componentWillMount

declarations.comments: Extend a `Spec` with a display name.
declarations.title: displayName

declarations.comments: Create a component class from a `Spec`.
declarations.title: createClass

declarations.comments: Render a component class to the document body.
declarations.title: render

declarations.comments: Render a component class to the specified node.
declarations.title: renderTo

modules.name: Thermite.Action
modules.comments:
This module defines the `Action` monad, which can be used to access the 
component state, and invoke asynchronous actions in the `Eff` monad.

declarations.comments:
The `Action` monad, parameterized by 

- The row of effects which are allowed in its asynchronous actions
- The component state type
- The return type
declarations.title: Action

declarations.comments: Run a computation in the `Action` monad.
declarations.title: runAction

declarations.comments: Get the current component state.
declarations.title: getState

declarations.comments: Update the component state.
declarations.title: setState

declarations.comments: Modify the component state by applying a function.
declarations.title: modifyState

declarations.comments:
Run an asynchronous computation.

The first argument is a function which takes a callback, and starts some asynchronous computation,
invoking the callback when the result is available.
declarations.title: async

declarations.comments: Run a synchronous computation.
declarations.title: sync

declarations.comments:
Set the component state based on the result of an asynchronous computation.

The first argument is a function which takes a callback, and starts some asynchronous computation,
invoking the callback when the new state is available.
declarations.title: asyncSetState

modules.name: Thermite.Events
modules.comments: This module defines helper functions for creating event handlers.

modules.name: Thermite.Html
modules.comments: This module defines functions for creating simple HTML documents.

declarations.comments: Create a text node.
declarations.title: text

declarations.comments: Create a HTML element from a tag name, a set of attributes and a collection of child nodes.
declarations.title: createElement

declarations.comments: Create a HTML document from a component class
declarations.title: component

modules.name: Thermite.Types
modules.comments: This module defines types used by the Thermite library.

declarations.comments:
The `Context` type represents React's `this` reference.

It is passed to event handlers to allow us to get and set component state.
declarations.title: Context

declarations.comments:
A component class, the result of React's `createClass` method.

The type parameters capture the properties required by the class, and the effects
its action handlers can have.
declarations.title: ComponentClass

declarations.comments: The type of HTML attributes.
declarations.title: Attr

declarations.comments: The type of HTML elements.
declarations.title: Html
